Ingredients:
	100-150 g finely chopped white mushrooms
	1 cup (180-200 g) long rice
	2 tbsp olive oil
	1 tsb salt
	1 cube chicken bouillon
	2 cups water
	1 tsbp basil (ri7an)
	1/4 tsp black pepper
	1/3 cup chopped onions
	3 big cloves garlic (chopped)

Heat the olive oil in a pan, then add the onions, fry for 2 minutes. add the garlic and the mushrooms, fry for another 2 minutes, add the washed rice, fry for 2 more minutes, then add the water, and basically everything else. Stir for 1 minute, when boiling turn to low heat, cover, and remove when all water is gone.

